"A vital function of the financial system is to shift risk, but that is mos=
tly=C2=A0a euphemism. Finance can't make risks go away, or even really move=
 them all that much. When the financial system shifts the risk of X=C2=A0ha=
ppening from Y=C2=A0to Z, all that means is that Z=C2=A0gives Y=C2=A0money =
if X happens. If X was going to happen to Y, it's still going to happen to =
Y. But now Y gets money.=C2=A0Death is a central fact of human existence, t=
he=C2=A0fundamental datum that gives meaning to life, but it is also a risk=
 -- you never know when it will happen! --=C2=A0and so the financial=C2=A0i=
ndustry has figured out=C2=A0ways to shift it. Not in any=C2=A0supernatural=
=C2=A0sense, I mean, but in the regular financial-industry sense: by giving=
 people money=C2=A0when death happens to them. One cannot know for certain =
how much of a consolation that is.""Another vital function of the financial=
 system is to brutally punish the mispricing of risk through arbitrage. Act=
ually=C2=A0I don't really know how vital that=C2=A0one=C2=A0is, but people =
are pretty into it. If someone under- or overestimates a risk, someone else=
 will find a way to make them pay for it. That's how markets, even the mark=
et for death, stay efficient.""The normal way to shift the risk of death is=
 life insurance -- you die, the insurance company gives you money -- but th=
ere are other, more esoteric versions, and they are more susceptible to arb=
itrage.One=C2=A0version=C2=A0involves=C2=A0"medium and long-term bonds and =
certificates of deposit ('CDs') that contain 'survivor options' or 'death p=
uts.'"=C2=A0Schematically, the idea is that a financial institution issues =
a bond that pays back=C2=A0$100 when it matures=C2=A0in 2040 or whatever. B=
ut if the buyer of the bond dies, he gets his $100 back immediately,=C2=A0i=
nstead of having to wait until 2040. He's still dead, though."[end of parti=
al quote]
AP ('Assassination Politics'; =C2=A0https://cryptome.org/ap.htm =C2=A0) =C2=
=A0can be considered to be 'death arbitrage' with a few key differences: =
=C2=A0The person who will die isn't part of the agreement, and doesn't prof=
it when the initial deal is struck, nor later. =C2=A0=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =
=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 Jim Bell




